{{afc comment|Wikidata entry [[d:Q838918]] Wikidata name: 2nd day of the 3rd month in the Chinese calendar [[User:Immanuelle|Immanuelle]] ([[User talk:Immanuelle|talk]]) 08:01, 11 June 2025 (UTC)}} {{Not to be confused with|March 2|qq=March 2}}[[Category:Days of the Japanese Lunisolar Calendar]]<!--why is this category always showing up as 347 members?--> {{afc comment|1=This article as with the other date articles is relatively limited in scope to Japan. Reviewing the translation of this is good and also adding content translated from Chinese and Korean wikipedias will also be good. Both wikipedias are also relatively centered around their own countries for their Lunisolar calendar dates[[User:Immanuelle|Immanuelle]] ([[User talk:Immanuelle|talk]]) 00:16, 28 April 2025 (UTC)}} {{Globalize|article|Japan|date=April 2025}} {{Expand Chinese|1=三月初二|topic=hist|date=April 2025}} {{Expand Korean|1=음력 3월 2일|topic=hist|date=April 2025}} {{Lunisolar March|qq=}} '''March 2''' is the 2nd day of the month {{ill|March (Lunisolar)|ja|3月 (旧暦)|lt=March (Yayoi)|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/March (Lunisolar)|qq=}}, the 3rd month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=}}. Its {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Rokuyō|qq=}} day is {{ill|Butsumetsu|ja|仏滅|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Butsumetsu|qq=}}.
== Events == * [[:en:Empress Jitō|Empress Jitō]] 9th year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:695|695]] [[:en:April 19|April 19]]) – In this year, the king of [[:en:Silla|Silla]] sent a prince as an envoy to Japan.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://example.com|title=Reference needed|accessdate=2021-03|qq=}}</ref> * [[:en:Engen|Engen]] 1st year / [[:en:Kenmu|Kenmu]] 3rd year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1336|1336]] [[:en:April 13|April 13]]) – In the battle of Tatara-hama, after being chased from Kyoto, [[:en:Ashikaga Takauji|Ashikaga Takauji]] defeated Kikuchi Takefusa at Chikuzen Tatara-hama and resumed his eastward advance. * [[:en:Tenpō|Tenpō]] 11th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1840|1840]] [[:en:April 4|April 4]]) – Under the appointment of [[:en:Mizuno Tadakuni|Mizuno Tadakuni]], the office of the Kanjō Bugyō was transferred to the position of the Kita-machi Bugyō.
== Births == * [[Tendoku (Japan)|Tendoku]] 3rd year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:959|959]] [[:en:April 12|April 12]]) – [[:en:Emperor En'yū|Emperor Enyū]], the 64th Emperor of Japan (died [[:en:991|991]]). * [[:en:Ryakuō|Ryakuō]] 1st year / [[:en:Engen|Engen]] 3rd year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1338|1338]] [[:en:March 23|March 23]]) – [[:en:Emperor Go-Kōgon|Emperor Gōgen]], the 4th Emperor of the Northern Court (died [[:en:1374|1374]]). * [[:en:Kannin|Kansei]] 3rd year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1791|1791]] [[:en:April 4|April 4]]) – {{ill|Ansekong Saensai|ja|安積艮斎|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ansekong Saensai|qq=}}, a Confucian scholar (died [[:en:1861|1861]]).
== Deaths == * [[Chishō]] 3rd year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1179|1179]] [[:en:April 10|April 10]]) – [[:en:Shunkan|Shunkwan]], a monk (died [[:en:1143|1143]]). * [[:en:Meitoku|Meitoku]] 3rd year / [[:en:Genchū|Genchū]] 9th year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1392|1392]] [[:en:March 25|March 25]]) – [[:en:Hosokawa Yoriyuki|Hosokawa Yoriyuki]], a military commander and official (died [[:en:1329|1329]]). * [[:en:Tenshō (Momoyama period)|Tenshō Era]] 10th year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1582|1582]] [[:en:March 25|March 25]]) – [[:en:Nishina Morinobu|Ninashi Morinobu]], a military commander (died [[:en:1557|1557]]?).
